{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Settled Status for EU citizens who contributed as key workers during Covid-19.",
        "additional_details": "We call upon the government to recognize their service. \r\n\r\nFrance rewarded frontline immigrant workers with fast-track application procedures; https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-55423257 \r\n\r\nIt is time we, too, show appreciation by offering EU citizens, who have not met the 5-year residency requirement for Settled Status, the opportunity to apply for Settled Status after:\r\n-3 years of continuous residency in the UK.\r\n-Being actively engaged in the national effort during Covid-19 as a key worker.",
        "background": "Extend Settled Status to all EU citizen with Pre-Settled Status who contributed to our national effort against Covid-19.\r\nMany EU nationals decided to remain in the UK and have tirelessly worked in healthcare, the food industry, logistics, and beyond, in service of the public good.",
